# UTF-8 encoding (Windows)

Cursor/VS Code on Windows sometimes saves files as **UTF-16 LE**, which breaks Node, dotenv, Next.js, and PostCSS (null bytes, invalid exports).

## Rules

1. All text files must be **UTF-8 without BOM**.
2. After creating or editing files, run `npm run encoding:check`.
3. If check fails, run `npm run encoding:fix` before committing.
4. Prefer writing files via Node (`writeFile(..., 'utf8')`) or PowerShell UTF-8 when bulk-fixing on Windows.

## PowerShell one-liner (manual fix)

```powershell
$utf8 = New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false
$text = [IO.File]::ReadAllText($path, [Text.Encoding]::Unicode)
[IO.File]::WriteAllText($path, $text, $utf8)
```

## Git hook (one-time setup)

```bash
git config core.hooksPath .githooks
```
